summary: Doctor Who according to someone who's never seen it
title: Doctor Who according to someone who's never seen it
body:
I'm a member of the Supernatural and the Sherlock fandom (among others), and I have yet to actually watch Doctor Who. My cousin, however, has seen it, and she asked me to answer some questions about Doctor Who for fun. Here are some of my answers. These are the ones she either a) laughed the most at, or b) said you guys might find humorous.
-----------------------------------------------------------
1. What's the Doctor's name?: I legitimately thought he was actually called 'Doctor Who' until I saw where some people were making fun of Catherine Tate for thinking the same thing. So I don't know. [*laughs* Are you gonna at least guess?] I'm just gonna call him Robert because I don't think he has a real name.
2a. Can you name any of the actors who have played him?: David Tennant.
2b. Okay, any others?: There's a woman, right? Jodie something...Whittaker? And I believe there was one called Matt Smith but that's probably fake. It sounds like I just tried to make up a very British sounding name.
3a. How long's it been on the air?: I dunno...Granddad said he watched it back in the '60s, so probably at least fifty years, but I don't think it's been on continuously.
3b. Why do you say that?: Because they're only on number 13, right? That and I read somewhere Supernatural is currently the longest running continuous sci-fi show, and it's been on for only 14 years. Also, Sherlock--which is also by the BBC of course--has been on almost ten years and only has 4 season, so...in British television maths, I think that probably adds up. [So fuckin' weird]
4. What's a Tardis?: A blue police box that can time travel, right? [Yeah] For visiting aliens? [*deadpan* What] Right? [Next question]
5. What's a Dalek?: Isn't that what R2D2 is or something? They're related? [...I...I don't know, maybe] It's the little robot thing though? [Sure]
6. Who is Rose Tyler?: Is she the Doctor's wife? [*laughing*] Not the Doctor's wife? [Not exactly]
7. What do you know about angels?: I know the Supernatural fandom likes them but...Doctor Who fans don't? [Why?] Something about blinking? [What about blinking?] No idea.
8. Is the Tardis a boy or a girl?: I thought it was a mode of transportation. [It's been a person before.] Has it? Eh...probably a girl. [Right.] And they won't make the Impala a person...discrimination.
9. How many Doctors have there been?: Like...technically only one, right? Just different actors? [Oh shit...you're right...How many?] Thirteen? [Okay]
10. One last one *shows me a picture of what I assume to be the inside of the Tardis* What's this?: Looks like that fair ride we went on that spins you around and makes it where you can't move off the wall and then the seat things slam you into the ceiling. [That's oddly specific] It looks like they converted that into a little computer room. [Okay, you're done]

tags: not for the faint of heart
title: Haven - Chapter Two
body:
A Bad Samaritan fic

Fandom: Bad Samaritan, Cale Erendreich

Rating: Explicit

Word Count: 2600

Summary: 14 Years Ago - Valkenberg is free again and ready to start living his own life away from the clutches of his tyrannical parents. Despite his repeated stays in mental institutions, he has certain tastes that lead him down a dark path, and there, in a seedy sex club in Portland, he meets a young woman who slowly but surely shows him his true destiny.

He clapped once, and she stood up straight, waiting for his command.

“You will clean yourself,” he said, then did an about face. She followed him without a word into a small bathroom. The walls were rough cedar, but the room was fitted with a proper tub, and multiple bottles of very expensive toiletries gleamed on the shelves in the shower.

“Yes, Mr. V,” she said, and shed her stained dress.

He gave her an appreciative glance, then looked in the mirror. He frowned at the muddy fingerprints on his shoulder, and started unbuttoning his shirt. She turned on the shower, and he stomped his foot hard on the floor. She jumped.

“You’re absolutely filthy. How did you surmise that a shower would be enough?” he said, and turned off the water. He grabbed a big handful of her hair and guided her to the clawfoot tub at the other side of the bathroom, in front of a window. Involuntary tears of pain streaked her muddy cheek. He gave her another long look, his eyes soft. A muddy tear dripped on the pristine white of the tub.

“I’m sorry, Mr. V,” she said, and sniffled. Her vision was blurry with pain, but her eyes still lingered on the line of his neck, and his chest. His nipples were taut with the cold. Or maybe, with arousal. She licked her lips. He slapped her back to the present.

“You will clean yourself,” he said, then did an about face. She followed him without a word into a small bathroom. The walls were rough cedar, but the room was fitted with a proper tub, and multiple bottles of very expensive toiletries gleamed on the shelves in the shower.

“Yes, Mr. V,” she said, and shed her stained dress.

He gave her an appreciative glance, then looked in the mirror. He frowned at the muddy fingerprints on his shoulder, and started unbuttoning his shirt. She turned on the shower, and he stomped his foot hard on the floor. She jumped.

“You’re absolutely filthy. How did you surmise that a shower would be enough?” he said, and turned off the water. He grabbed a big handful of her hair and guided her to the clawfoot tub at the other side of the bathroom, in front of a window. Involuntary tears of pain streaked her muddy cheek. He gave her another long look, his eyes soft. A muddy tear dripped on the pristine white of the tub.

“I’m sorry, Mr. V,” she said, and sniffled. Her vision was blurry with pain, but her eyes still lingered on the line of his neck, and his chest. His nipples were taut with the cold. Or maybe, with arousal. She licked her lips. He slapped her back to the present.
